    "title": {
        "rendered": "Meeting Across the River: Bruce Springsteen and Willie Nile, &#8220;One Guitar&#8221;"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>Willie Nile&#8217;s &#8220;One Guitar&#8221; won the AIM Independent Music Award for Best Social Action Song in 2013. It was well deserved. Willie&#8217;s metaphor for the power of the individual is tailor-suited for Bruce, and the two have performed it together at three Light of Day concerts over a four-year span.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s the most recent one, from 2015:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wI-WmKdRRkc?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8230;along with Willie&#8217;s original, one of the great rock anthems.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/6_YBsy_HtWg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Update 1/25/2020:</strong></p>\n<p>Bruce and Willie reprised their Light of Day &#8220;One Guitar&#8221; duet last week in Asbury Park, and it was a fantastic performance. Take it in below:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/DWKZzyuYC1U?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>One Guitar<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> January 14, 2012 (Asbury Park, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> January 18, 2020 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>Bruce and Willie Nile team up on Willie&#8217;s rock anthem &#8220;One Guitar&#8221; at Light of Day 2015.</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
